<p data-end="414" data-start="383"><strong data-end="414" data-start="383">Last Updated: July 15, 2026</strong></p>

<p data-end="578" data-start="416">Tactical Equipment Hub respects the privacy of its visitors. This Privacy Policy explains how information may be collected, used, and handled when you visit our website.</p>

<h2 data-end="605" data-section-id="1pmvrr9" data-start="580">Information We Collect</h2>

<p data-end="743" data-start="607">Tactical Equipment Hub does not directly require visitors to create an account or provide personal information to read our articles and guides.</p>

<p data-end="1056" data-start="745">When you access the website, basic technical information may be processed automatically by our hosting, security, or analytics service providers. This information may include your IP address, browser type, device information, operating system, referring page, pages visited, and the date and time of your visit.</p>

<p data-end="1238" data-start="1058">If you voluntarily contact us or submit information through a communication method made available on the website, we may use the information you provide to respond to your inquiry.</p>

<h2 data-end="1265" data-section-id="1usefoo" data-start="1240">How We Use Information</h2>

<p data-end="1536" data-start="1267">Information collected through the website may be used to operate and maintain the website, understand how visitors interact with our content, improve website performance and user experience, respond to inquiries, and protect the website from misuse or security threats.</p>

<h2 data-end="1573" data-section-id="cghl20" data-start="1538">Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>

<p data-end="1750" data-start="1575">The website or third-party services used to operate it may use cookies or similar technologies to support website functionality, measure traffic, and understand website usage.</p>

<p data-end="1870" data-start="1752">Cookies can store or communicate information about visits and browsing activity.</p>

<p data-end="1991" data-start="1872">You may control or delete cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect certain website features.</p>

<h2 data-end="2016" data-section-id="1nkfe3v" data-start="1993">Third-Party Services</h2>

<p data-end="2217" data-start="2018">Tactical Equipment Hub may use third-party hosting, analytics, security, or other website service providers. These providers may process limited technical information as necessary to provide their services.</p>

<p data-end="2302" data-start="2219">Their handling of information is governed by their own terms and privacy practices.</p>

<h2 data-end="2321" data-section-id="1hmz97v" data-start="2304">External Links</h2>

<p data-end="2432" data-start="2323">Our articles and guides may contain links to external websites, products, resources, or third-party services.</p>

<p data-end="2623" data-start="2434">Tactical Equipment Hub does not control the content, security, or privacy practices of third-party websites. Visiting an external website is subject to that website&#39;s own terms and privacy policy.</p>

<p data-end="2737" data-start="2625">We encourage visitors to review the privacy policies of external websites before providing personal information.</p>

<h2 data-end="2777" data-section-id="1s4tkcj" data-start="2739">Editorial and Informational Content</h2>

<p data-end="2926" data-start="2779">Tactical Equipment Hub is an independent informational resource publishing practical guides, product insights, equipment advice, and educational articles.</p>

<p data-end="3041" data-start="2928">References or links to third-party websites do not mean that Tactical Equipment Hub operates or controls those websites.</p>

<h2 data-end="3064" data-section-id="1jzz3es" data-start="3043">Children&#39;s Privacy</h2>

<p data-end="3182" data-start="3066">Tactical Equipment Hub is intended for a general audience and is not directed specifically to children under the age of 13.</p>

<p data-end="3431" data-start="3184">We do not knowingly seek to collect personal information from children under 13. The FTC&#39;s COPPA rules impose specific requirements on covered websites that collect personal information from children under 13.</p>

<h2 data-end="3449" data-section-id="vy6skj" data-start="3433">Data Security</h2>

<p data-end="3637" data-start="3451">We take reasonable steps to support the security and operation of the website. However, no method of transmitting or storing information online can be guaranteed to be completely secure.</p>

<h2 data-end="3672" data-section-id="1mbig7f" data-start="3639">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

<p data-end="3768" data-start="3674">We may update this Privacy Policy when our website, services, or information practices change.</p>

<p data-end="3853" data-start="3770">Any updated version will be posted on this page with a revised &quot;Last Updated&quot; date.</p>

<h2 data-end="3865" data-section-id="a2jb2d" data-start="3855">Contact</h2>

<p data-end="3997" data-start="3867">Questions regarding this Privacy Policy may be submitted through any contact method made available on the Tactical Equipment Hub website.</p>
